<figureCitation id="22E82A2CFFF6B008C05BF811FE73EAB1" box="[328,435,1976,2003]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–12. 1–4" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1886,1910]" captionTargetBox="[264,1426,464,1851]" captionTargetId="figure-125@3.[148,1439,450,1860]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1–12. 1–4. Microserica nicobarensis (Redtenbacher, 1868); 5–8. Maladera reyaensis Bhunia, Gupta, Chandra &amp; Ahrens, new species; 9–12. Nepaloserica cheemaensis Bhunia, Gupta, Chandra &amp; Ahrens, new species. (1, 5, 9) Aedeagus in lateral view (left); (2, 6, 10) Aedeagus in dorsal view; (3, 7, 11) Aedeagus in lateral view (right); (4, 8, 12) Habitus, dorsal view. Scale 0.5 mm; habitus not to scale." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5778764" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5778764/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="595">Figs. 1–3</figureCitation>
